The '''Emperor's Reach''' was an exalted level of [[Dark side adept/Legends|Dark Side Adept]] loyal to [[Emperor/Legends|Emperor]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]]&mdash;also known as [[Darth/Legends|Darth]] Sidious, the reigning [[Dark Lord of the Sith/Legends|Dark Lord of the Sith]]. They had the unique ability to communicate across great distances with [[The Force/Legends|the Force]].

==History==
The Emperor's Reach was a position which served in a parallel with the [[Emperor's Hand/Legends|Emperor's Hands]], [[Emperor's Eye]]s, and [[Emperor's Voice (Galactic Empire)|Emperor's Voice]]. Palpatine entrusted the training of one member to the [[Prophets of the Dark Side|Prophets]] of the [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|Dark Side]], the member having previously been one of their own.<ref name="Evil">{{Hyperspace|url=hyperspace/member/insideronline/88/indexp2.html|text=''Evil Never Dies: The Sith Dynasties''|int=Evil Never Dies: The Sith Dynasties}}</ref>

[[Maarek Stele/Legends|Maarek Stele]] was a member of this secretive organization, having been recruited from the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[Imperial Navy/Legends|Navy]].<ref name="TIE Fighter">[[Star Wars: TIE Fighter (video game)|''Star Wars: TIE Fighter'']]</ref>

